This paper deals with distributed computation in dynamic networks, which is a topic that falls under the categories of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses Peer-to-Peer (P2P) networks, which are a type of network infrastructure that falls under the category of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). Additionally, the paper deals with the problem of adversarial churn, which is a security-related issue that falls under the category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper proposes randomized algorithms, which are a type of algorithmic technique that falls under the category of Systems and Control (cs.SY).
